title: Newborn triplets diagnosed with coronavirus but their parents tested negative
description: A set of premature triplets born in Mexico are "stable" and "evolving favorably" after testing positive for Covid-19, according to local health officials.

title: Trump event speaker criticized for calling Aunt Jemima a 'picture of the American dream'
description: A speaker at President Donald Trump's Arizona event is being criticized over comments she made calling Aunt Jemima a "picture of the American Dream."

title: Novak Djokovic's folly is a lesson to the world
description: "From day one of the organization of the Adria Tour, we've been following the rules and the measures that have been regulated by government institutions and health public institutions," Novak Djokovic said last week before the Croatia leg of Adria, a tennis tournament he'd organized for charity. "We've been through all these processes and the result of it all was amazing."

title: This may be America's first known wrongful arrest involving facial recognition
description: The American Civil Liberties Union has filed an administrative complaint with Detroit's police department over what the advocacy organization claims is the country's first known wrongful arrest involving facial-recognition technology.

title: Race car driver posthumously named fastest woman on Earth for attempt that killed her
description: She's officially the fastest woman on Earth.

title: 'He was going to burn alive': Bystander describes intense rescue caught on video
description: A bystander and a sheriff's deputy in California pulled a man out of a burning truck to safety.

title: Trump's latest moves aren't exactly a winning economic -- or reelection -- strategy
description: President Donald Trump's latest economic policies are the opposite of the emergency aid that Corporate America and Wall Street are clamoring for.

title: A huge dust plume from the Sahara Desert is closing in on the US
description: A dust plume from the Sahara Desert traveled across the Atlantic and is darkening skies in the Caribbean. One model predicts it will reach the Southeastern and Mid-Atlantic US.

title: Republican policing reform measure collapses in Senate
Drone video shows surfers' very close encounter with great white shark
description: South Africa's sea rescue service has urged swimmers and surfers to be cautious, after a recent spate of great white shark sightings and close encounters -- one of which was captured in some astonishing drone footage.

title: Watch hearing go off the rails when lawmaker keeps banging table
description: Rep. Louie Gohmert (R-TX) refused to quit banging the table after House Judiciary Chairman Jerrold Nadler (D-NY) gave a witness extra time to finish his opening statement.

title: Angry residents erupt at meeting over new mask rule
description: Residents of Palm Beach County in Florida erupted in anger at a commissioner's meeting after an unanimous vote to make masks mandatory.

title: China's GPS rival Beidou is now fully operational
description: China launched the last satellite in its Beidou navigation network on Tuesday, completing a new rival to GPS and cementing its place in an elite group of countries with their own global navigation satellite systems (GNSS).

title: This New Hampshire town's voting system is 130 years old
description: The town of Windsor, New Hampshire, has been using the same paper ballot box for 130 years and election officials say it's one of the safest ways to vote.

title: Paris Fashion Week is going ahead in September
description: Paris Fashion Week will go ahead this fall, the event's organizers have confirmed, with shows starting September 28.

title: WHO Special Envoy to US: Please take this virus very seriously
description: CNN's Hala Gorani speaks with World Health Organization Special Envoy Dr. David Nabarro, who warns that as countries prepare to ease lockdowns they need to do so carefully and take the virus seriously.

title: Pope writes letter of support to Paralympic champ after horrific crash
description: Pope Francis has sent a letter to ex-Formula One driver and Paralympic champion Alex Zanardi, who remains in intensive care after suffering a horrific cycling crash on Friday.

title: This may be the secret behind Beijing's quick virus response
description: CNN's David Culver goes into a mass coronavirus testing site in Beijing as the capital city tries to maintain control over the most recent Covid-19 outbreak.

title: CNN anchor on possible travel ban: EU is not messing around
description: As European countries prepare to reopen their borders to international travel, US travelers may be banned from entering. CNN's Richard Quest explains why the EU is considering blocking travelers from the US as US Covid-19 cases continue to rise.

title: Dr. Gupta: We're in the middle of a huge problem right now
description: CNN Chief Medical Correspondent Dr. Sanjay Gupta raises the alarm with New Day's Alisyn Camerota over the rising state of the novel coronavirus in the nation.

title: He joined a seminary at 19. Then he began exploring his sexuality
description: Mark Tedesco joined a seminary in Rome when he was a teenager. Halfway through his education, he began to confront feelings he'd had for much of his life -- feelings he wasn't sure how to reconcile with his faith. See more from CNN's "Life After" series.

title: This event usually involves millions, this year it's reducted to around 1,000
description: Saudi Arabia will strictly limit the number of people who can take part in this year's Hajj pilgrimage to Mecca because of the coronavirus. CNN's Sam Kiley reports.

title: Several US states are reporting thousands of new coronavirus cases each day
description: Officials are making desperate calls on residents to stay home, wear a mask and keep their distance after alarming coronavirus trends have emerged across several US states.

title: Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez wins Democratic primary, CNN projects
description: Freshman Democratic Rep. Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez will defeat former longtime CNBC correspondent and anchor Michelle Caruso-Cabrera in a Democratic primary election on Tuesday for New York's 14th Congressional District, CNN projects.

title: Political newcomer beats Trump's pick in North Carolina GOP congressional primary
Trump's brother takes legal action to block tell-all book by President's niece
description: President Trump's younger brother filed a temporary restraining order on Tuesday in an attempt to block the publication of an unflattering tell-all book by the President's niece, Mary L. Trump.

title: Charleston is removing a statue of slavery defender and former Vice President John C. Calhoun
description: Crews in Charleston, South Carolina, began the process of removing a statue of John C. Calhoun in the early hours of Wednesday morning, according to a tweet from the police department.

title: EU considers denying entry to American visitors over US failure to contain coronavirus
Trump ignores viral surge while using crisis as racist punchline
The US President is using the worst domestic crisis in decades as a racist punchline
description: President Donald Trump's top health advisers say that the coronavirus pandemic has driven America to its knees amid a disturbing surge in cases. But Trump is ignoring the new danger, instead using the worst domestic crisis in decades as a racist punchline.

title: Castle employees play house -- and clean toilets -- in grand estate closed to visitors
description: Laura Jamieson and Michael Smith fell in love while working in an 800-year-old castle. But they never expected to live at their place of employment.

title: Black Lives Matter protests have not led to a spike in coronavirus cases, research says
description: Despite warnings from public health officials, new research suggests Black Lives Matter protests across the country have not led to a jump in coronavirus cases.

title: Porn star charged with sexually assaulting four women
description: Porn star Ron Jeremy has been charged with forcibly raping three women and sexually assaulting another in separate incidents dating back to 2014, Los Angeles County District Attorney Jackie Lacey announced Tuesday.

title: Empathy is both a trait and a skill. Here's how to strengthen it
description: Having empathy is crucial to fostering strong relationships. What better time than now to strengthen your abilities to express different types of empathy? Here's how to strengthen that skill and practice it in your everyday life.

title: Some cyberbullies show signs of PTSD, according to a UK study
description: Cyberbullying is linked to a variety of post-traumatic stress disorder symptoms, not only in victims but cyberbullies as well, according to a new study of over 2,000 UK teens. Over a quarter of cyberbullies suffer from post-traumatic stress disorder symptoms.

title: Should you take a supplement to prevent disease?
description: Eating a healthy diet far outweighs the potential benefits of taking a supplement, experts say, and yet we have a whole industry based on selling us all types of products. Here's when to take one, after consulting with your doctor, and when to pass.

title: Brazil judge orders President Jair Bolsonaro to wear a face mask in public
description: Brazil's president Jair Bolsonaro has been ordered by a federal judge in Brasilia to wear a face mask in public or face a fine.

title: The country where hundreds of thousands of people haven't heard of Covid-19
description: Hundreds of thousands of people trapped near fierce fighting in Myanmar's far west may know nothing of Covid-19 thanks to a yearlong internet shutdown, according to rights groups.

title: A teenager accused of killing her alleged sex trafficker is released from jail on $400,000 bond
description: A Wisconsin teenager accused of killing her alleged sex trafficker was released from jail Monday on $400,000 bond, according to the organization that paid for her release.

title: FBI provides details on rope found in Bubba Wallace's garage
description: NASCAR driver Bubba Wallace says he's "pissed" members of the public are now questioning his integrity after the FBI said a noose found in his garage stall this week was there before his team moved in.

title: An 8-year-old girl, her mother and her grandfather drown in their new home's swimming pool
description: An 8-year-old girl, her mother and grandfather found dead in the pool of their New Jersey home died as a result of accidental drowning, the medical examiner's office said Tuesday.

title: Trudeau attacks China's 'political' detention of two Canadians
description: The decision by China to charge two Canadians with espionage was clearly political, the country's Prime Minister, Justin Trudeau, said Tuesday, after a top Chinese diplomat warned him to "stop making irresponsible remarks" about the case.

title: Read powerful letter high school student wrote on why she won't wear name of her school on her jersey
description: Trude Lamb, an incoming high school sophomore, has won countless medals for her school's cross country team. But with each victory and celebratory picture, she is painfully reminded of the name that runs across her chest -- Robert E. Lee.

title: Political newcomer beats Trump's pick in North Carolina GOP congressional primary
description: A 24-year-old political newcomer will defeat President Donald Trump's endorsed candidate in the North Carolina GOP congressional primary for the seat vacated by the President's chief of staff, Mark Meadows, CNN projects.

title: Trump admin says they're against mail-in ballots. CNN anchor has the receipts.
description: CNN's Don Lemon compares President Donald Trump's accusations and false claims about mail-in ballots being linked to voter fraud to his administration's history of using absentee ballots to cast their own votes.

title: EU considers denying entry to American visitors after US failure to contain coronavirus
What if Trump rejects the 2020 election result?
description: It's hard for Americans to imagine that a president who lost a bid for re-election would refuse to leave office. But in recent weeks some analysts have done more than imagine it: they've begun to explore what can be done if Donald Trump does just that. What, they ask, if he claims that widespread election fraud marred the voting or rejects the result of a close race.

title: Police officer involved in Breonna Taylor's death has been fired
description: A police officer involved in the March fatal shooting of Breonna Taylor in Louisville, Kentucky, has been fired, according to the police department.

title: Cooper: Trump is pretending the virus has passed
description: CNN's Anderson Cooper sounds off on President Trump's barrage of coronavirus comments downplaying the pandemic, despite the growing number of cases throughout the nation.

title: Doctor on Trump rally: A scene like that is really upsetting
description: CNN's Erin Burnett speaks with Dr. Murtaza Akhter as President Donald Trump holds a rally in Phoenix while coronavirus cases continue to rise across the US.
